subSubSection.paragraph:
Cephalothorax
: Carapace (
Fig. 4A, C
) yellow, long oval, longer than wide, widest at coxae II and III; with a dark brown pattern between ocular area and fovea, slightly constricted at the position of half length; fovea inconspicuous. Sternum yellowish. Labium reddish brown. Chelicerae (
Fig. 8C, D
) reddish brown, with six promarginal peg teeth and two retromarginal teeth. Endites deep brown, longer than wide. Leg color similar to carapace, with irregular dark stripes (
Fig. 4I, J
).

